China has allocated 200 million yuan for disaster relief following a deadly earthquake in the southwest that claimed over 8,700 lives.
The magnitude 7.8 quake struck densely populated areas in Sichuan province, with the worst impact since 1976.
Russian President Dmitry Medvedev offered condolences and assistance to China.
Despite no warning signs detected before the earthquake, the death toll in Sichuan alone reached 8,533.
Rainfall poses challenges to relief efforts, with international support pouring in from countries like Germany, Norway, and Belgium.
Ethnic minorities affected by the disaster will receive targeted aid.
